{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01UKC8esTYWMaxcvwMjztS9C","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The error is clear:\n\n```\nExtended key usage does not permit use for TLS client authentication\n```\n\nThe certificate I generated has `extendedKeyUsage=serverAuth` only. For ES transport TLS, the certificate needs to also support `clientAuth` because nodes authenticate each other (mutual TLS). The ES transport layer uses the same certificate for both server and client authentication.\n\nI need to:\n1. Regenerate the TLS certificate with both `serverAuth` AND `clientAuth` in the Extended Key Usage\n2. Update the secret\n3. Restart the StatefulSet pods\n\nLet me regenerate the certs with proper EKU.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":9812,"cache_read_input_tokens":51747,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":9812},"output_tokens":21,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0406e1a2-236f-48f3-a2b3-94bc9a85fba7","uuid":"f8b5c9e4-9cfd-4bf9-9968-cb7ed734dc99","request_id":"req_011CcerbiyNSQ8tJ1ADL8tXb"}
